<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="motivation-n">motivation <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌməʊtɪ'veɪʃn/    美 /ˌmoʊtɪ'veɪʃn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>积极性；动力</strong></h4>
<p>the enthusiasm for doing sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>These methods can help <strong>improve</strong> / <strong>increase</strong> students’ <strong>motivation</strong> and interest.
这些方法能帮助增强学生的积极性和兴趣。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>动机；诱因</strong></h4>
<p>the need or reason for doing sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Escape can be a strong <strong>motivation for</strong> travel.
逃避现实可以成为旅游的一种强烈动机。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Her motivation <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ writing was a desire for women to get the right to higher education.  （2014 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. for  </p></div>